# Backend-scoped Semgrep ignore list. Mirrors the relevant entries from the
# repo-root .semgrepignore so semgrep behaves the same whether invoked from
# the repo root (local dev) or from apps/backend/ (bin/ci, RWX ci-backend).
#
# RWX's ci-backend filter intentionally does NOT include the repo-root
# .semgrepignore — the file in this directory is what gets materialized into
# the cloud workspace.

# Test-scaffolding layer — excluded from production wheels (see
# apps/backend/pyproject.toml [tool.hatch.build.targets.wheel]) and gated by
# `is_dev_env()` at the HTTP boundary. Test helpers legitimately use patterns
# (DB TRUNCATE, hardcoded fake secrets, set_*_for_tests seam imports) that
# Semgrep flags as risky in production code.
app/testing/
**/app/testing/

# Test files themselves (real code is covered by surrounding rules)
test_*.py
**/test/test_*.py

# Migrations — autogenerated alembic output
**/alembic/versions/
